3
00:01:31,530 --> 00:01:34,030
Nine hundred years ago...?

4
00:01:34,660 --> 00:01:36,740
What are you talking about?!

5
00:01:36,740 --> 00:01:40,580
Are you saying a futuristic city
like this existed back then, too?!

6
00:01:40,960 --> 00:01:43,040
It's just a theory.

7
00:01:43,710 --> 00:01:47,250
There was a man who once
risked his life for archaeology...

8
00:01:47,880 --> 00:01:50,550
to shed light on that ancient kingdom.

9
00:01:50,550 --> 00:01:56,470
And... machinery excavated from a particular site
dates back to that kingdom's reign.

10
00:01:59,890 --> 00:02:04,100
That machine was built
during the Void Century?!

11
00:02:05,060 --> 00:02:07,570
How much do you know, exactly?

12
00:02:07,570 --> 00:02:08,690
– Huh?
– Huh?

13
00:02:08,690 --> 00:02:11,030
Robin! You know about this?!

14
00:02:11,030 --> 00:02:13,990
I'm sure it's painful to remember...

15
00:02:14,490 --> 00:02:17,950
but twenty-two years ago,
your home, Ohara...

16
00:02:17,950 --> 00:02:21,830
was destroyed by a Marine buster call.

17
00:02:22,710 --> 00:02:23,790
This is my theory:

18
00:02:24,420 --> 00:02:29,750
Ohara was destroyed because
it discovered that kingdom's existence.

19
00:02:32,260 --> 00:02:34,300
The Void Century...

20
00:02:34,930 --> 00:02:38,810
is the history of a conflict between
that highly advanced kingdom...

21
00:02:38,810 --> 00:02:41,390
and an alliance of twenty kingdoms.

22
00:02:50,980 --> 00:02:53,280
Those twenty kingdoms emerged victorious,

23
00:02:53,650 --> 00:02:58,490
and founded the World Government,
creating the world as we know it today.

24
00:02:58,870 --> 00:03:03,120
Then, in order to ensure that the ideals of
that kingdom were never passed down,

25
00:03:03,580 --> 00:03:06,960
they erased it from history completely.

26
00:03:06,960 --> 00:03:09,170
What...? That's crazy...!

27
00:03:09,170 --> 00:03:12,130
H-Huh?! Are you serious?!

28
00:03:14,470 --> 00:03:17,510
What a thrilling tale!

29
00:03:17,510 --> 00:03:20,220
Wait a minute, Vegapunk!

30
00:03:20,220 --> 00:03:23,350
If they sounded a buster call
on Ohara for that...

31
00:03:23,350 --> 00:03:26,560
that means the people who learn about it...

32
00:03:26,560 --> 00:03:28,770
Yeah, they'll be erased.

33
00:03:30,900 --> 00:03:34,280
Hey! Why did you even tell us?!

34
00:03:34,280 --> 00:03:35,650
Dammit!

35
00:03:35,650 --> 00:03:38,160
I heard every word he said!

36
00:03:38,160 --> 00:03:40,490
I can't unhear it...

37
00:03:40,490 --> 00:03:41,870
Time to forget!

38
00:03:41,870 --> 00:03:43,490
I know nothing!

39
00:03:43,490 --> 00:03:45,960
I didn't hear it! I don't know it!

40
00:03:45,960 --> 00:03:48,250
No thoughts! Just forget!

41
00:03:45,960 --> 00:03:47,580
Calm down a little.

42
00:03:48,250 --> 00:03:50,710
I heard nothing! Nothing at all!

43
00:03:48,750 --> 00:03:50,710
I said it was just a theory.

44
00:03:52,250 --> 00:03:53,710
This is horrible!

45
00:03:53,710 --> 00:03:55,170
I don't wanna die!

46
00:03:55,760 --> 00:03:57,800
However, Nico Robin...

47
00:03:58,380 --> 00:04:02,560
if Ohara was destroyed for this theory...

48
00:04:02,560 --> 00:04:05,810
isn't the government
basically admitting it's true?

49
00:04:05,810 --> 00:04:08,640
Whose side are you on, exactly?

50
00:04:08,640 --> 00:04:14,110
The scholars of Ohara studied precious
historical texts to arrive at that theory...

51
00:04:14,110 --> 00:04:17,700
Wouldn't the government
tell someone as high up as you?

52
00:04:17,700 --> 00:04:19,570
No, they haven't told me anything.

53
00:04:19,570 --> 00:04:21,780
It's the same for everyone.

54
00:04:21,780 --> 00:04:25,830
Discussing this would result in
my erasure, regardless of my affiliation.

55
00:04:27,210 --> 00:04:29,290
Then I don't wanna know!

56
00:04:29,290 --> 00:04:31,830
This is like torture!

57
00:04:31,830 --> 00:04:33,630
Get me outta here!

58
00:04:33,630 --> 00:04:37,760
Then how did you learn about the kingdom?!

59
00:04:37,760 --> 00:04:41,640
All the books Ohara collected
from across the world... were...

60
00:04:42,260 --> 00:04:44,140
The will of Ohara lives on.

61
00:04:44,680 --> 00:04:49,310
The events of that day
threw the world into confusion.

62
00:04:49,310 --> 00:04:54,610
The island of scholars, Ohara,
with the most advanced knowledge in the world,

63
00:04:55,020 --> 00:04:58,650
was destroyed in a single day,
save for one little girl...

64
00:05:02,450 --> 00:05:04,990
The scholars were labeled
as a group of devils...

65
00:05:04,990 --> 00:05:07,290
seeking to overthrow the World Government.

66
00:05:09,500 --> 00:05:11,420
Several months after the incident...

67
00:05:12,210 --> 00:05:14,340
I visited Ohara.

68
00:05:14,880 --> 00:05:19,670
I was somewhat acquainted with
Professor Clover, an authority on archaeology.

69
00:05:20,340 --> 00:05:22,130
so I wanted to leave flowers.

70
00:05:22,510 --> 00:05:24,100
You knew him?!

71
00:05:24,100 --> 00:05:25,050
Yeah.

72
00:05:26,180 --> 00:05:28,930
He was obsessed with the Void Century...

73
00:05:31,690 --> 00:05:35,980
enough to set off on adventures
to scour the world for related texts.

74
00:05:36,360 --> 00:05:40,950
The Marines arrested and jailed him
no fewer than ten times...

75
00:05:42,570 --> 00:05:44,160
There he is!

76
00:05:44,570 --> 00:05:48,620
It made him the most famous
archaeologist in the world.

77
00:05:49,450 --> 00:05:54,790
Eventually, word of his exploits
drew scholars to Ohara,

78
00:05:54,790 --> 00:05:58,920
which became a haven for archaeology.

79
00:05:59,380 --> 00:06:02,170
One might say his talent
is what caused that tragedy.

80
00:06:03,380 --> 00:06:06,100
When I set foot on Ohara,

81
00:06:06,100 --> 00:06:08,310
the place was in ruins.

82
00:06:11,480 --> 00:06:14,350
Even the Tree of Knowledge
had burned to the ground...

83
00:06:14,350 --> 00:06:17,610
with everything around it reduced to ash.

84
00:06:20,110 --> 00:06:23,650
But as I walked deeper into the island,

85
00:06:24,530 --> 00:06:27,120
I witnessed something astonishing.

86
00:06:27,950 --> 00:06:29,910
What is all of this?!

87
00:06:30,540 --> 00:06:33,040
A vast amount of books of all kinds...

88
00:06:33,040 --> 00:06:36,540
were submerged in the lake
at the center of the island!

89
00:06:36,960 --> 00:06:42,420
I believe that the scholars stood their ground,
even as the buster call burned their home,

90
00:06:42,420 --> 00:06:45,550
and died ensuring their legacy
would reach the future.

91
00:06:46,890 --> 00:06:51,310
The books that all of those
scholars risked their lives for...

92
00:06:51,930 --> 00:06:56,980
Ignorant Marines wouldn't understand
their value, even if they found them.

93
00:06:57,690 --> 00:06:59,270
Ohara won.

94
00:06:59,820 --> 00:07:01,610
When I saw that,

95
00:07:01,610 --> 00:07:04,740
I couldn't stop the tears from flowing.

96
00:07:06,200 --> 00:07:07,280
Please take Robin!

97
00:07:07,620 --> 00:07:09,780
My daughter must escape the island!

98
00:07:09,780 --> 00:07:10,490
What?!

99
00:07:10,490 --> 00:07:12,410
No! What about you, Mom?!

100
00:07:12,410 --> 00:07:13,790
Aren't you coming with me?!

101
00:07:15,040 --> 00:07:17,290
Olvia, what are you...?

102
00:07:18,170 --> 00:07:21,500
There's still something
that I have to do here, so...

103
00:07:22,000 --> 00:07:25,260
Mom! Don't leave me!

104
00:07:25,260 --> 00:07:27,010
I'll stay here too!

105
00:07:27,010 --> 00:07:28,510
Robin...

106
00:07:28,510 --> 00:07:31,600
As an Oharan scholar,
you should understand this well.

107
00:07:32,140 --> 00:07:34,270
History is the legacy of mankind.

108
00:07:34,270 --> 00:07:35,140
Put out the fire!

109
00:07:35,140 --> 00:07:36,230
Protect the books!

110
00:07:36,230 --> 00:07:38,060
Save as many books as we can!

111
00:07:38,060 --> 00:07:40,520
Throw the books out of the library!

112
00:07:40,980 --> 00:07:43,320
Ohara doesn't want to expose our history.

113
00:07:43,650 --> 00:07:46,990
We only wished to preserve
the voices of the past.

114
00:07:47,610 --> 00:07:50,450
Our research ends here...

115
00:07:51,160 --> 00:07:53,410
but even if Ohara is obliterated...

116
00:07:53,410 --> 00:07:55,580
we cannot forsake...

117
00:07:56,120 --> 00:07:59,380
the future of your generation!

118
00:08:00,580 --> 00:08:02,380
I don't understand!

119
00:08:03,800 --> 00:08:06,130
You will... someday.

120
00:08:08,800 --> 00:08:09,470
Now...

121
00:08:10,470 --> 00:08:11,510
go, Saul!

122
00:08:15,810 --> 00:08:17,440
Are you sure about this?

123
00:08:17,980 --> 00:08:19,150
Yes.

124
00:08:19,150 --> 00:08:23,980
I don't wanna go!
I wanna stay with you, Mom!

125
00:08:23,980 --> 00:08:26,860
Mom!

126
00:08:28,240 --> 00:08:30,570
Live, Robin!

127
00:08:36,410 --> 00:08:38,290
Hold your head high, Robin!

128
00:08:38,290 --> 00:08:40,880
Your mom is honorable!

129
00:08:40,880 --> 00:08:45,920
Someday, pass down
this island's history, Robin!

130
00:08:45,920 --> 00:08:50,010
Ohara fought against the world!

131
00:08:55,220 --> 00:08:57,850
What's the matter, Robin?

132
00:08:57,850 --> 00:09:01,730
Hey! How dare you make
Robin cry, you bucket head!

133
00:09:01,730 --> 00:09:04,110
That's it, Vegapunk!

134
00:09:04,110 --> 00:09:07,070
Get these shoes off me so I can kick your ass!

135
00:09:02,610 --> 00:09:04,900
You're so insensitive, Vega!

136
00:09:07,070 --> 00:09:08,190
Get 'em off!

137
00:09:08,190 --> 00:09:10,570
Pay attention, bucket head!

138
00:09:15,330 --> 00:09:16,540
Vegapunk.

139
00:09:17,870 --> 00:09:19,660
It's like you thought.

140
00:09:20,410 --> 00:09:23,170
Ohara uncovered
the existence of that kingdom.

141
00:09:23,170 --> 00:09:25,340
I see. Then it is true.

142
00:09:25,750 --> 00:09:29,010
Where are the books from the lake now?

143
00:09:29,010 --> 00:09:32,680
I wanted to bring them back to Punk Hazard,

144
00:09:32,680 --> 00:09:35,260
but I couldn't risk
the higher-ups hearing about it.

145
00:09:35,850 --> 00:09:37,260
To tell you the truth...

146
00:09:37,260 --> 00:09:40,140
I met some people that day.

147
00:10:02,540 --> 00:10:05,040
Who'd be here in ruins like these?

148
00:10:06,500 --> 00:10:08,300
Pull it up!

149
00:10:10,550 --> 00:10:13,010
Giants?!

150
00:10:13,380 --> 00:10:15,720
What are they up to?

151
00:10:15,720 --> 00:10:18,810
Are they aware of the value of these books?!

152
00:10:19,520 --> 00:10:20,270
The books...

153
00:10:22,100 --> 00:10:24,440
What are they gonna do with them?!

154
00:10:24,440 --> 00:10:25,770
That head of yours...

155
00:10:26,730 --> 00:10:30,030
It's as big as ever. I'd recognize it anywhere.

156
00:10:39,830 --> 00:10:42,830
It's been a while, Vegapunk.

157
00:10:45,750 --> 00:10:47,790
Dragon?!

158
00:10:48,290 --> 00:10:52,380
Your head got bigger again.

159
00:10:56,970 --> 00:10:58,510
Never mind that!

160
00:10:58,890 --> 00:11:00,640
Why are you here?!

161
00:11:00,640 --> 00:11:03,810
That's my question, Vegapunk.

162
00:11:03,810 --> 00:11:07,610
I knew old man Clover.

163
00:11:07,610 --> 00:11:10,610
Oh? You, too?

164
00:11:10,610 --> 00:11:11,440
Well...

165
00:11:12,030 --> 00:11:15,990
he used to be a hooligan
adventuring all over the place.

166
00:11:16,030 --> 00:11:19,280
That nonsense about him
trying to destroy the world...

167
00:11:19,280 --> 00:11:21,490
is poppycock and propaganda!

168
00:11:22,120 --> 00:11:23,370
Yeah.

169
00:11:26,210 --> 00:11:29,210
Are you wondering what they're doing?

170
00:11:29,210 --> 00:11:33,420
I can't let them steal those valuable books!

171
00:11:33,420 --> 00:11:35,510
They're not bandits.

172
00:11:35,510 --> 00:11:37,380
I've already checked them out.

173
00:11:37,380 --> 00:11:38,390
What?

174
00:11:40,100 --> 00:11:42,770
They came from Elbaph.

175
00:11:43,140 --> 00:11:45,730
They know the value of the books.

176
00:11:49,560 --> 00:11:54,650
Their captain is a strange man
with bandages all over his body...

177
00:11:56,490 --> 00:11:59,870
He said, "The Oharans saved their
legacy by sacrificing their lives,

178
00:11:59,870 --> 00:12:03,120
and I won't let it be erased from history."

179
00:12:11,790 --> 00:12:15,170
It's a good thing that you
government people...

180
00:12:15,170 --> 00:12:18,180
didn't find and destroy the books first.

181
00:12:18,180 --> 00:12:19,430
Hey, wait!

182
00:12:19,430 --> 00:12:20,720
I would never...!

183
00:12:20,720 --> 00:12:22,720
I thought it was a joke!

184
00:12:22,720 --> 00:12:26,180
I couldn't believe you'd actually
become a government lapdog.

185
00:12:28,020 --> 00:12:31,770
And after turning down our invitation
to join the Freedom Fighters, too...

186
00:12:33,150 --> 00:12:34,480
Don't be stupid!

187
00:12:34,480 --> 00:12:37,490
Even with my talent and intellect,

188
00:12:37,490 --> 00:12:40,780
what could I create in
a poorly funded outfit like yours?!

189
00:12:41,780 --> 00:12:43,240
I get it.

190
00:12:43,240 --> 00:12:46,120
You're as blunt as ever.

191
00:12:46,120 --> 00:12:48,870
The World Government is
an enormous organization.

192
00:12:48,870 --> 00:12:52,000
The Marines, especially,
are full of reasonable people.

193
00:12:52,630 --> 00:12:55,460
Don't lose sight of the goal, Dragon.

194
00:12:56,170 --> 00:12:57,720
I know, but...

195
00:12:59,220 --> 00:13:02,340
this incident really shook me.

196
00:13:03,140 --> 00:13:09,060
A group of harmless scholars
were violently eradicated...

197
00:13:09,060 --> 00:13:11,440
simply for questioning that absurd "law"!

198
00:13:14,110 --> 00:13:17,360
But I'm going to raise
an army that can fight back!

199
00:13:17,860 --> 00:13:20,200
I thought you despised war!

200
00:13:20,820 --> 00:13:22,950
Just you wait, Vegapunk.

201
00:13:22,950 --> 00:13:25,030
I'm going to change the world!

202
00:13:25,740 --> 00:13:27,330
I won't let Clover's death...

203
00:13:28,080 --> 00:13:31,460
or the will of Ohara go to waste!

204
00:13:33,040 --> 00:13:35,790
Later that year, Dragon teamed up with...

205
00:13:36,500 --> 00:13:38,960
Emporio Ivankov...

206
00:13:40,550 --> 00:13:42,630
and Bartholomew Kuma...

207
00:13:43,840 --> 00:13:46,350
to create the Revolutionary Army...

208
00:13:47,220 --> 00:13:49,220
that now shakes the world!

209
00:13:53,270 --> 00:13:55,980
Luffy's dad is so ambitious!

210
00:13:55,980 --> 00:13:58,940
Wait just a second! Did you say Elbaph?!

211
00:13:58,940 --> 00:14:03,410
I didn't know Dragon and
Professor Clover knew each other...!

212
00:14:03,410 --> 00:14:07,830
That bastard Iva was a founding member
of the Revolutionary Army?

213
00:14:09,120 --> 00:14:11,500
I feel like my brain's gonna explode!

214
00:14:11,500 --> 00:14:14,670
Why did Kuma help us?!

215
00:14:14,670 --> 00:14:18,590
Why did you modify him, Vegapunk?!

216
00:14:18,920 --> 00:14:23,680
While it's true the government
must not find Ohara's books...

217
00:14:29,720 --> 00:14:33,350
I secretly went to Elbaph anyway
for reasons of my own.

218
00:14:38,270 --> 00:14:40,980
I read every document there.

219
00:14:42,780 --> 00:14:43,530
So...

220
00:14:44,110 --> 00:14:46,740
the mystery of the world
that Ohara unraveled...

221
00:14:47,700 --> 00:14:49,870
lives on in my brain...

222
00:14:49,870 --> 00:14:53,750
and I've been continuing their research.

223
00:14:53,750 --> 00:14:56,670
Can I ask you one thing?

224
00:14:57,580 --> 00:14:59,710
That giant captain...

225
00:14:59,710 --> 00:15:01,960
His name was...

226
00:15:07,260 --> 00:15:09,510
Saul, wasn't it?

227
00:15:12,220 --> 00:15:15,190
He's in hiding now.

228
00:15:15,190 --> 00:15:17,900
I must keep it a secret from everyone.

229
00:15:24,780 --> 00:15:27,530
Thank you, Vegapunk...

230
00:15:27,530 --> 00:15:30,990
for not allowing Ohara's
struggle to be for nothing.

231
00:15:31,370 --> 00:15:34,410
I'm simply well versed in all areas of study.

232
00:15:34,410 --> 00:15:36,870
It's the way of a true scholar.

233
00:15:48,890 --> 00:15:51,890
The shoes are moving on their own!

234
00:15:56,940 --> 00:16:00,150
I can't release you yet.
You'll have to come with me.

235
00:16:00,860 --> 00:16:03,150
There's something I want to show you.

236
00:16:03,780 --> 00:16:06,990
Hey! There's no cockpit
on this thing, Chopper.

237
00:16:07,910 --> 00:16:10,700
I got it! Maybe this robot...

238
00:16:10,700 --> 00:16:12,910
moves on its own!

239
00:16:12,910 --> 00:16:16,330
Maybe it'll react if we say something to it!

240
00:16:16,660 --> 00:16:18,460
Like... Like...

241
00:16:18,460 --> 00:16:21,130
Move! Move, robot!

242
00:16:21,920 --> 00:16:22,960
It didn't work...

243
00:16:22,960 --> 00:16:25,460
I wonder what the magic word is...

244
00:16:25,460 --> 00:16:27,930
No! It must have a name!

245
00:16:27,930 --> 00:16:29,840
We should call it out!

246
00:16:29,840 --> 00:16:32,100
Move, Robonosuke!

247
00:16:34,810 --> 00:16:36,560
Robo King!

248
00:16:36,560 --> 00:16:37,850
Jeez...

249
00:16:37,850 --> 00:16:39,480
What are you guys, kids?

250
00:16:39,480 --> 00:16:41,650
That obviously won't work.

251
00:16:50,200 --> 00:16:51,910
What?!

252
00:17:02,920 --> 00:17:04,420
Are you okay?

253
00:17:04,420 --> 00:17:05,670
Yeah...

254
00:17:05,670 --> 00:17:08,220
What was that?! Did the robot explode?!

255
00:17:08,220 --> 00:17:10,930
No, it wasn't an explosion.

256
00:17:10,930 --> 00:17:13,800
Then what just happened?!

257
00:17:14,350 --> 00:17:17,720
Hey!

258
00:17:17,720 --> 00:17:20,560
Help me-quasar!

259
00:17:21,690 --> 00:17:23,020
"Quasar"?

260
00:17:23,020 --> 00:17:24,150
Oh no!

261
00:17:24,150 --> 00:17:25,520
I failed again!

262
00:17:25,520 --> 00:17:28,740
Somebody, help me-quasar!

263
00:17:28,740 --> 00:17:32,200
Maybe I warped space-time when I teleported!

264
00:17:32,200 --> 00:17:34,320
Was that old man there before?

265
00:17:34,320 --> 00:17:36,410
I don't think so.

266
00:17:33,820 --> 00:17:36,410
I'm sinking! Hey!

267
00:17:36,410 --> 00:17:38,790
My body's sinking!

268
00:17:38,790 --> 00:17:40,410
Somebody!

269
00:17:43,630 --> 00:17:45,630
I don't know what's going on.

270
00:17:45,630 --> 00:17:48,010
Hey, gramps, do you need help?

271
00:17:53,300 --> 00:17:55,890
Help me-quasar!

272
00:17:55,890 --> 00:17:57,310
What the...?

273
00:17:57,310 --> 00:17:59,640
You're just like Kin'emon.

274
00:18:01,440 --> 00:18:04,190
Hurry up!

275
00:18:07,400 --> 00:18:09,280
I'll get you out!

276
00:18:09,280 --> 00:18:10,400
Thanks!

277
00:18:14,200 --> 00:18:15,410
I knew it!

278
00:18:15,410 --> 00:18:16,410
It's him!

279
00:18:18,660 --> 00:18:19,790
Thank you!

280
00:18:19,790 --> 00:18:21,120
By the way, you're...

281
00:18:21,120 --> 00:18:22,870
Dragon's son, right?

282
00:18:22,870 --> 00:18:24,460
I knew you were here.

283
00:18:24,460 --> 00:18:26,250
I'm glad you came.

284
00:18:26,250 --> 00:18:27,460
And you must be...

285
00:18:27,460 --> 00:18:28,750
Bonney!

286
00:18:28,750 --> 00:18:30,460
You're all grown up!

287
00:18:30,460 --> 00:18:31,920
Vegapunk!

288
00:18:32,670 --> 00:18:34,680
I'm glad to see you doing well!

289
00:18:35,890 --> 00:18:37,890
Old man, are you floating?!

290
00:18:38,390 --> 00:18:40,270
You're wearing them, too.

291
00:18:40,270 --> 00:18:40,970
What?

292
00:18:40,970 --> 00:18:44,690
Those dom shoes have a hover function!

293
00:18:44,690 --> 00:18:47,440
What?! A hover function?!

294
00:18:47,440 --> 00:18:48,650
How do we use it?!

295
00:18:48,650 --> 00:18:52,320
First, press the button on the side...

296
00:18:53,070 --> 00:18:54,530
Oh, this one.

297
00:18:55,110 --> 00:18:57,070
And this lever!

298
00:18:57,070 --> 00:19:00,040
Push it down!

299
00:19:00,040 --> 00:19:00,870
Like this?!

300
00:19:01,450 --> 00:19:02,620
That's it!

301
00:19:11,050 --> 00:19:13,510
We flew too high!

302
00:19:15,680 --> 00:19:19,970
Help me-quasar!

